Acquisition of Genomic Data and Metadata from GenBank

GenBank is the NIH genetic sequence database, an annotated collection of all publicly available DNA sequences (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/genbank/).

Params:
    Sequence (str): The taxon of the virus genome to be acquired
    Data format (str): The format of the data to be acquired
    Date (str): The date after which the data was released (e.g. '01/01/2010')
    Command line arguments (list): Additional command line arguments to be passed to the NCBI datasets command

Sequence alignment for Dengue serotypes
configfile: "config/config.yaml"
from grapevne_helper import import_grapevne

grapevne = import_grapevne(workflow)
globals().update(vars(grapevne))


# Set up a rule if concrete targets are specified
try:
    if param('targets'):
        rule target:
            input:
                expand(
                    output("Aligned_{target}/nextalign.aligned.fasta"),
                    target=param('targets')
                ),
except ValueError:
    pass


rule sequence_alignment:
    input:
        sequences=input("Unaligned_{serotype}.fasta"),
        reference=resource("reference_genomes/reference_{serotype}.fasta"),
        genemap=resource("genemap/genemap_{serotype}.gff"),
    output:
        fasta=output("Aligned_{serotype}/nextalign.aligned.fasta"),
    log:
        log("sequence_alignment_{serotype}.log"),
    conda:
        env("alignment.yaml")
    message:
        "Running sequence alignment for Dengue serotypes"
    params:
        output_serotype=output("Aligned_{serotype}"),
        resources_dir=resource(''),
    shell:
        """
        mkdir -p {params.output_serotype}
        nextalign run \
            {input.sequences} \
            --reference={input.reference} \
            --genemap={input.genemap} \
            --output-fasta={output.fasta} > {log} 2>&1
        """


rule _test:
    input:
        output("Aligned_Dengue_1/nextalign.aligned.fasta"),

Segregating E gene and Whole Genomes and performing quaility control

This module takes aligned virus sequences and segregates the envelope gene (EG) and whole genomes (WG). It then performs quality control on the sequences.

Params:
  WG Threshold (number): Whole Genome Threshold
  EG Threshold (number): Envelope Gene Threshold
  Serotypes (list of str): List of serotype names (e.g. Dengue_1, etc.)
